CONVERSATION TITLE: Clinical Data Scientist (Cancer Research/SAS) – Top $$/Remote
SUBJECT: Clinical Data Scientist (Cancer Research/SAS) ��� Top $$/Remote
CONTENT: Hello, Our client, an NC organization that operates a data sharing platform for cancer research, is actively recruiting for a highly skilled candidate to join its Technical Operations and Client Support team.  This organization, committed to the advancement of cancer research technique, makes cancer research data available to researchers around the world.  The platform holds real-world and clinical trial data and this role will involve working with researchers/users to get them acclimated to the system as well as provide Analytical support and insight.  This is a critical (and impactful) role and company will pay generously to attract a star.    Key Things to Note: •	Position involves two primary functions – Data Analytics and Platform Operations. Both require extensive client engagement and we seek an Analyst who will optimize the user experience •	The Cancer Research Programs involve unique and voluminous data sets that include clinical trial and real-world data.  Experience working with both will be important, as will knowledge of CDISC •	SAS is a critical partner and SAS tools are heavily used. Seek candidate with SAS coding skills as well as knowledge of advanced analytics tools (VDMML).  •	Role may also involve image work and Convolutional Neural Networks. Python, R, postGreSQL, SQL, C/C++ would be a plus •	Platform Operations functions focus on the overall management of the platform including user onboarding, troubleshooting, configuration optimization, etc. Seek candidate who will embrace these functions. •	This position can be remote (East Coast).  Client is open to both Direct Hire and Contractor candidates  Many more details are available.    This organization is important work and we seek the skilled, can-do and mission-driven candidate who will help all of the stakeholders achieve their goals.  Let me know if this might be of interest to you.  For now, I thank you for your time.   Best, Lee Frankel leef@frankelstaffing.com

SUBJECT: Job Opportunity for a  Device Characterization Engineer - San Jose, CA.
CONTENT: Hello, Greetings  Hope you are doing good!  We have a job opening for an Device Characterization Engineer - San Jose. and It's a full-time opportunity.   Client : Power Integrations(PI).  Description :   Participate in the development of world-class high-voltage power devices and analog/mixed signal process technologies in a fabless environment. Characterize high-voltage power devices, low and medium voltage MOSFETs, Bipolars and other analog components using both ATE and other test equipment. Develop test capabilities to meet new device characterization requirements.   Responsibilities :  Develop test programs in the ATE to characterize PCM structures. Correlate results with foundry provided data.  Develop test programs for characterizing new devices in development.  Process raw characterization data and provide converted data in a Spotfire/Excel friendly format.  Transfer test programs between different ATE and correlate results to ensure good accuracy.  Automate data collection procedures on multiple test equipment in the lab.    Requirements:  BS in Electrical Engineering preferred.  A minimum of 2 years’ experience in semiconductor device and technology development.  Hands-on experience with ATE/wafer prober such as Keithley S530 and other characterization tools in the lab.  Basic understanding of semiconductor device physics.  Strong communication and collaboration skills  New College Grad with right background (coursework + internship) could be considered.  Krish Konathala Senior Talent Acquisition Specialist

SUBJECT: Sr. Data Scientist Job Opportunity
CONTENT: Hi Tolu -   Happy Tuesday! After reviewing your LinkedIn, I think you would be a great fit for a Data Scientist position I have available with one of my enterprise level clients. I have included an overview of the position below. I would love to discuss this position further. Please let me know when you are available to connect.   An Insight Global client is looking to add a Sr. Data Scientist to their team in the Perimeter/Sandy Springs area. The Sr. Data Scientist will be joining the Analytics Center of Excellence (ACOE). This role will be responsible for advanced analytics solutions design and implementations. This candidate will be responsible for working on projects spanning across the organization for transaction reductions. The Sr. Data Scientist will be responsible for discovery/exploratory analyses in order to find project opportunities within existing data and teaching the stakeholder news ways to build out solutions. Proficiency in Python coding (pandas, numpy, scipy, scikit-learn) for machine learning and/or NLP is required. Proficiency in SQL is also required.   Must Haves:  • 3+ years of experience in advanced analytics role in machine learning, artificial intelligence, natural language processing, research, predictive analytics or similar area  • Strong programming skills and ability to utilize a variety of data/analytic software/languages/tools; Python (pandas, numpy, scipy, scikit-learn) • Experience writing and executing queries of enterprise databases via SQL coding  • Experience with visualization tools such as Tableau, Power BI, or AWS Quicksight  • Experience creating/performing ETL processes – ideally in an AWS environment  • Exposure to AWS in professional or personal projects: services such as Glue, Athena, Sagemaker, lambda, Redshift, EC2, EMR, Kinesis, Neptune, S3, etc.  Brianna Johnson Information Technology Account Manager at Insight Global

That way, I can keep you in the loop on relevant market trends.  For instance, I'm working with a local healthcare system that is looking to hire a data analyst for a 2 month, fully remote engagement. At the end of the engagement there is a cash bonus.   Within the healthcare system, their Office of Community Affairs forges purposeful partnerships with its neighbors in the region, with a particular focus on the Durham community by connecting partners with campus efforts, research, and institutional resources. They support community partnerships through financial contributions, grants, and sponsorships; service and volunteerism; and charitable activities and employee giving. They focuse on nutrition and food security, housing affordability and infrastructure, early childhood and school readiness, college and career-readiness, and non-profit capacity-building.  This person will help streamline the data in SQL and then visual the key points (in Tableau) for the digital platform for community outreach partners to view. This will help the company to  align resources to high need areas in the community.   I have no idea what your career goals are, but I’d like to understand them. Does this sound like something you’d be interested in? If not, what types of emerging technologies and market trends would you like to be kept in the loop on?    Best,  Caitlin LaForce, MS Matching Software Developers with the Best Opportunities

The way Wanted works is that as a talent, you just set your salary. Companies will reach out blind via Wanted only based on locations, skills & min. salary.  That is when you (as a talent) will know about the company. You will get a page with all the details (committed salary of course but also perks, equity, project, team etc...)  Then, only if you accept to reveal your profile, they will know more about you (like who you are). If you don't like the offer, your profile keeps being anonymous.  Keep in mind that companies working with us pay +30% over the market because we don't take any placement fees.

SUBJECT: Data Analyst III-Durham
CONTENT: Title: Data Analyst III Nature: Contract-to-hire Location: RTP, NC  Job Description:  Our client, is a company that’s actively expanding its data and analytics capabilities and, most of all, the way we think about data as an asset. The primary purpose of this role is to assist data visualization leaders to connect to customers and develop priority data visualization tools. This role will build connection points between datasets, enabling the creation of priority cross-functional reporting for the business. Work with the data visualization leaders to develop strategies for sustainable data delivery and reporting. Connect with Portfolio and Analytics & Data Sciences teams to prioritize and implement these strategies.    Required Qualifications: • Bachelor's Degree in Business, Economics, Math, or related field • 2+ year(s) of experience in data analytics focused on identifying and solving business problems; ability to analyze a wide variety of data, including financial data to inform strategic decision making • 2+ year(s) experience with SQL, R, Python, or other languages • 2+ year(s) of experience with Power BI, Qlik, or Tableau • Knowledge and experience in connecting to and navigating relational databases • Experience designing and prototyping visualizations for large and complex data sets with demonstrated business application • Comfortable working on cross-functional teams ccountabilities:  • Translate business requirements, multiple data sets, KPIs, and other data points into relevant dashboards, reports, and analytics solutions • Implement and maintain reporting capabilities using PowerBI, Qlik, Tableau, and other reporting applications • Data source identification, data aggregation, data curation • Robust iterative approach to development, employing stakeholder engagement to achieve business requirements  Sommer McCabe Technical Recruiter at Procom

SUBJECT: A message from CGL Recruiting
CONTENT: Hello all,  As a first level connection of mine I thought you might like an update on what my firm is trying to do to support you and the many other job seekers in these unprecedented times.  Most of the data I am receiving from our clients seems to say that things will be picking up in the late summer time frame.    While I wish we had positions to place you all in through our clients, that is not realistic.  I am still committed to trying to help as I can.  To this end, as a first level connection to me, if I see positions that are open that I think you might be interested in, I am trying to tag you to those posts.  If you would prefer I not do this for you, please let me know.  I believe most of you are aware of the free video series we have put together for job seekers.  There are now over 50 free videos out on YouTube with more coming out every day.  These videos are all designed to help you land a position quicker.  If you haven't seen them yet - here is the link:  https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC-qWGaepX8ZKQKnXAzkijgQ  I know the job search process is incredibly difficult.  You are not alone.  #weareallinthistogether  Take care.  Regards,  Melanie Woods, GPHR, SPHR, SHRM-SCP Managing Partner at CGL Recruiting mwoods@cglrecruiting.com www.cglrecruiting.com (832) 291-4405
